  "text": "Apache Kafka implements a comprehensive Startable/Stoppable service lifecycle pattern across its core broker, controller, and Connect components. The pattern is hierarchical and ensures coordinated startup and shutdown of dependent services.\n\n## Core Lifecycle Abstraction\n\nThe foundation is the `Server` trait (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/Server.scala:27) which defines three key methods:\n- `startup(): Unit` - Initialize and start the server\n- `shutdown(): Unit` - Gracefully shutdown the server\n- `awaitShutdown(): Unit` - Block until shutdown is complete\n\n## Startup Chain\n\n**KafkaRaftServer (entry point)** -> ControllerServer + BrokerServer:\nKafkaRaftServer.startup() (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/KafkaRaftServer.scala:90-98) orchestrates startup in the correct order:\n1. Starts the ControllerServer first (controller endpoints needed for broker)\n2. Then starts the BrokerServer\n3. Registers app info and metrics\n\n**BrokerServer.startup()** (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/BrokerServer.scala:189) starts in sequence:\n1. SharedServer.startForBroker() - initializes shared components\n2. KafkaScheduler.startup() - scheduler for background tasks\n3. LogManager initialization\n4. BrokerLifecycleManager creation\n5. SocketServer creation and configuration\n6. Replica manager, coordinators, and metadata publishers\n7. Request handlers startup\n8. State transitions to STARTED\n\n**ControllerServer.startup()** (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/ControllerServer.scala:123) starts:\n1. Dynamic configuration initialization\n2. Quota managers\n3. Metadata cache and publishers (KRaftMetadataCachePublisher, FeaturesPublisher)\n4. QuorumController instance\n5. SocketServer for controller APIs\n6. State transitions to STARTED\n\n**SharedServer** (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/SharedServer.scala) manages shared resources:\n1. startForBroker() or startForController() - coordinate single start\n2. Creates and starts KafkaRaftManager (core/src/main/scala/kafka/raft/RaftManager.scala)\n3. KafkaRaftManager.startup() initializes the Raft client and network channel\n4. MetadataLoader processes metadata updates\n\n## Shutdown Sequence (Reverse Order)\n\n**KafkaRaftServer.shutdown()** (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/KafkaRaftServer.scala:100-107) orchestrates shutdown:\n1. Shuts down BrokerServer first (may need controller for controlled shutdown)\n2. Then shuts down ControllerServer\n3. Unregisters app info\n\n**BrokerServer.shutdown()** (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/BrokerServer.scala:729-820) follows strict sequence:\n1. Optionally begins controlled shutdown (replicaManager and lifecycleManager)\n2. Begins shutdown of BrokerLifecycleManager\n3. Stops socket server request processors\n4. Metadata publishers cleanup\n5. Request handler pool shutdown\n6. Scheduler shutdown (CRITICAL - before LogManager to prevent concurrent operations)\n7. LogManager shutdown\n8. ReplicaManager shutdown\n9. Coordinator shutdown\n10. Final resource cleanup\n\n**ControllerServer.shutdown()** (core/src/main/scala/kafka/server/ControllerServer.scala:126) shuts down:\n1. SocketServer\n2. QuorumController\n3. Metadata publishers\n4. Request handlers\n5. Quota managers\n\n**RaftManager.shutdown()** (core/src/main/scala/kafka/raft/RaftManager.scala:171-179) cleanly closes:\n1. Expiration service\n2. Client driver\n3. Scheduler\n4. Network channel\n5. Replicated log\n6. Data directory locks\n\n## Java Scheduler Interface\n\nThe `Scheduler` interface (server-common/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/server/util/Scheduler.java:27) defines the pattern:\n- `void startup()` - Initialize scheduler\n- `void shutdown() throws InterruptedException` - Stop all scheduled tasks\n\n## Connect Framework Lifecycle\n\nKafka Connect implements similar patterns:\n\n**Connect** (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/Connect.java:35):\n- `start()` - Starts herder, REST server, and shutdown hook\n- `stop()` - Stops herder and REST server\n- `awaitStop()` - Blocks until shutdown complete\n\n**Herder** interface (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/Herder.java:63-68):\n- `void start()` - Start herder\n- `void stop()` - Stop herder\n\n**AbstractHerder** (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/runtime/AbstractHerder.java:180-192):\n- `startServices()` - Starts worker, statusBackingStore, configBackingStore\n- `stopServices()` - Stops services in reverse order, shuts down executor\n\n**Backing Stores** implement consistent lifecycle:\n- KafkaOffsetBackingStore.start() (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/storage/KafkaOffsetBackingStore.java:231) starts internal offsetLog\n- KafkaOffsetBackingStore.stop() (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/storage/KafkaOffsetBackingStore.java:260) stops offsetLog\n- FileOffsetBackingStore implements similar pattern\n\n**KafkaBasedLog** (connect/runtime/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/connect/util/KafkaBasedLog.java:220-286):\n- `start()` - Creates producer/consumer, reads to log end, starts work thread\n- `stop()` - Signals stop, joins thread, closes clients\n\n## Key Design Patterns\n\n1. **State Machine**: ProcessStatus enum (SHUTDOWN, STARTING, STARTED, SHUTTING_DOWN) with atomic transitions\n2. **Dependency Ordering**: Strict startup sequence ensures dependencies are ready before dependent components start\n3. **Reverse Shutdown**: Shutdown follows reverse of startup order to safely close dependent services first\n4. **Exception Safety**: Uses CoreUtils.swallow() to continue shutdown despite exceptions\n5. **Locking**: ReentrantLock and condition variables coordinate state transitions and await shutdown\n6. **Timeouts**: Deadline-based timeouts prevent indefinite blocking during startup/shutdown\n7. **Coordinated Startup**: SharedServer.startForBroker()/startForController() ensure single initialization of shared components\n8. **Graceful Shutdown**: Controlled shutdown protocol allows clean hand-off of responsibilities before hard stop"
